      "content": "i mean i know u have to say the doctor thing but i'm super busy with work this week and an urgent care visit will take hours. it just feels like a standard sprain tbh. if i just keep it elevated and ice it heavily for like 3 or 4 days do u think that should be enough to get the swelling down so i can walk again? i'd really rather just avoid the clinic if possible.",
